                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d801">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/6119.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Governor of Texas</gloss> to the <gloss
                            type="to">President</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Austin, Texas</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1913-02-12">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 12, 1913</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The continued disorders and the obligation of the United States to the world
                    under the Monroe doctrine makes it now a duty for our Government to intervene in
                    Mexico, not for conquest or territorial gain but to restore order and protect
                    life and property, and I respectfully urge this course without delay.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">O. B. Colquitt</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
